"WTI crude futures steadied near $94 per barrel on Friday but were set to end the week more than 5% higher amid various supply disruptions and expectations that fuel switching will boost demand. Six oil and gas fields in the Gulf of Mexico have been shut after a leak at a Louisiana booster station halted two pipelines, but major player Shell Plc said that it expected pipeline service to resume on Friday. Three of the six deepwater platforms owned by Shell produce a combined 410,000 bpd of oil. On the demand side, the IEA raised its forecast for global oil consumption this year to 2.1 million bpd, up by 380,000 from previous forecasts, citing surging natural gas prices and heat waves that incentivizes a switch to oil for power generation. The Paris-based agency also said that OPEC+ is unlikely to increase output significantly in the coming months due to limited spare capacity. This week’s gains follows a collapse in oil prices to six-month lows amid fears of a global economic slowdown."

library(dplyr) library(readr) company<-"CL=F" stDt <- as.Date(Sys.time()) endDt <- as.Date("2022-08-26") forecastBands <- c(-Inf,55,70,85,100,115,Inf) remainingCloses<-sum(!weekdays(seq(stDt, endDt, "days")) %in% c("Saturday", "Sunday")) histData<-read_csv( paste0( "https://query1.finance.yahoo.com/v7/finance/download/" , company , "?period1=946684800&period2=" , floor(as.numeric(as.POSIXct(Sys.time()))) , "&interval=1d&events=history&includeAdjustedClose=true" ) ) pricehistory<-as.numeric(histData$`Adj Close`) pricehistory<-pricehistory[!is.na(pricehistory)] pricehistory<-pricehistory[pricehistory>0] spot<-pricehistory[length(pricehistory)] sdMovementRatio <- sd(log(pricehistory[1:length(pricehistory)-1]/pricehistory[2:(length(pricehistory))])) simulation<-spot*replicate(10000, cumprod(exp(rnorm( remainingCloses,mean = 0, sd = sdMovementRatio )))[remainingCloses]) cutSimulation<-as_tibble(cut(simulation,forecastBands)) mutate(count(cutSimulation,value),n/sum(n))
